column5: CPRX I hate it when you go to a meeting and you come out and your gains have evaporated

CPRX Historically stocks have generally fallen during days leading up to holidays because traders offload their holdings in order to avoid the risk of significant news appearing while the markets are closed Stocks also tend to rally the week after a long holiday weekend Check historic charts and see for yourself Smart money tends to follow big money If institutions are dumping shares this week we can expect to see much more red before green
